                Since <m>t</m> divides <m>a</m>,
                there exists an integer <m>m</m> such that <m>\ldots </m>.
              </p>
            </li>
            <li>
              <p>
                Now let <m>a</m> and <m>b</m> be integers, not both zero,
                and let <m>d = \gcd(a, b )</m>.
                <xref ref="T_gcdaslincomb"></xref>
